						<h3>Bipolar Disorder</h3>
						<p>Bipolar disorder involves extreme mood swings, ranging from manic highs to depressive lows. Individuals may experience heightened energy, impulsivity, and grandiosity during manic episodes, followed by periods of profound sadness and lethargy.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="bottom-area-treatment">
				<div class="treatment-cnt">
					<ul>
						<li class="sub-heading">
							<h3>Symptoms:</h3>
							<p>Mood swings, impulsivity, increased energy during manic episodes, fatigue during depressive episodes.</p>
						</li>
						<li class="sub-heading">
							<h3>Causes:</h3>
							<p>trauma, neurotransmitter imbalances, environmental triggers.</p>
						</li>
						<li class="sub-heading">
							<h3>Types:</h3>
							<p>Bipolar I, Bipolar II, Cyclothymic disorder.</p>
						</li>
						<li class="sub-heading">
							<h3>Ways to Heal:</h3>
							<p>Mood stabilisers, psychotherapy, lifestyle management, support networks.</p>
						</li>
					</ul>
					<h5>You Can Learn Tools To Manage Bipolar Disorder And Become Less Affected By It.</h5>
